Swiss Super League side, FC Zurich have announced the signing of Nigeria midfielder, Ifeanyi Matthew. Matthew linked up with FC Zurich from Norwegian first division club, Lillestrøm SK. The former Flying Eagles star penned a two-year contract with the club. The 26-year-old scored 20 goals and recorded 18 assists in 196 appearances for Lillestrøm SK. He won the Norwegian Cup with the club in 2017. Mathew will wear jersey number 12 at FC Zurich.